info.description:
This API is in charge of any event-driven interaction with the Intellector server (that is, anything that cannot be achieved via REST endpoints).

Primary uses: online status check, notifications, in-game events.

Any message sent by a client must be a valid JSON having the following structure:
```
{
  "event": "name_of_the_event",
  "token": "authorization_token",
  "body": {...event payload conforming to the respective schema...}
}
```

Structure of the server-sent events is analogous:
```
{
  "event": "name_of_the_event",
  "body": {...event payload conforming to the respective schema...}
}
```

Valid client- and server-sent event names and their corresponding payload schemas are presented later in this specification.

Authorization token is obtained using the REST API /auth endpoints (there are one for guest authorization and one for logging in).
